('greenhouse', 'Greenhouse', 'Structured hiring software that builds fairer, more predictable recruiting pipelines',
 'Greenhouse is a recruiting platform designed around structured hiring - the practice of defining evaluation criteria before sourcing begins, applying them consistently to every candidate, and removing bias from hiring decisions through process design rather than willpower. Every job opening in Greenhouse starts with a defined scorecard listing the competencies and skills required. Interviewers score candidates against the same criteria using the same scale. The result is a dataset that predicts which attributes correlate with high performance at your company over time. Greenhouse integrations connect to 450+ HR tools including Slack, LinkedIn, Workday, and BambooHR, making it the center of gravity for most enterprise recruiting stacks. The CRM features let recruiting teams nurture passive candidates with targeted content, tracking engagement before a role opens. Greenhouse is used by companies including HubSpot, Squarespace, and Airbnb. For teams that are serious about reducing bias, improving offer acceptance rates, and building a predictable hiring engine, Greenhouse is the most mature platform in the category.',
 'https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=greenhouse.io&sz=64',
 'https://greenhouse.io', 'https://greenhouse.io',
 ARRAY['recruiting', 'hr-tech'],
 'paid', false, 0.00,
 4.5, 2841, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['Structured hiring scorecards reduce interview bias', 'Rich integration ecosystem - 450+ HR tools', 'CRM features for passive candidate nurturing', 'Strong analytics on pipeline conversion and source quality'],
 ARRAY['Enterprise pricing - not suitable for early-stage startups', 'Setup and configuration requires dedicated TA ops time', 'Reporting customization has a learning curve'],
 ARRAY['Running structured hiring at mid-market and enterprise scale', 'Building candidate pipelines before roles open via CRM', 'Tracking source quality and time-to-hire analytics'],
 NOW()),

('lever', 'Lever', 'Applicant tracking and CRM combined for relationship-first recruiting',
 'Lever combines an applicant tracking system and candidate relationship management into a single platform, built on the premise that every candidate is a future hire or future customer. The unified database means a candidate rejected for one role is automatically considered for future openings rather than lost in a folder. Lever Nurture runs automated email sequences to keep passive candidates warm over months - a critical capability in competitive hiring markets where the best candidates are rarely actively looking. The visual pipeline is clean and intuitive, making it accessible to hiring managers who interact with Lever occasionally rather than daily. AI features include automated job description writing, candidate fit scoring, and resume parsing that populates candidate profiles without manual data entry. Analytics dashboards track EEOC data, pipeline conversion by stage, and interviewer-specific pass-through rates. Lever is particularly popular at growth-stage tech companies and scale-ups that are hiring across multiple roles simultaneously and need recruiting to operate as a revenue function rather than an administrative one.',
 'https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=lever.co&sz=64',
 'https://lever.co', 'https://lever.co',
 ARRAY['recruiting', 'hr-tech'],
 'paid', false, 0.00,
 4.4, 1938, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['CRM and ATS in one platform - no separate tools needed', 'Lever Nurture automates passive candidate engagement', 'Clean visual pipeline accessible to non-recruiters', 'Strong EEOC and DEI reporting'],
 ARRAY['Custom enterprise pricing - no self-serve plan', 'Some reporting requires help from Lever support to configure', 'Mobile app less capable than desktop'],
 ARRAY['Managing high-volume hiring across 20+ open roles simultaneously', 'Running passive candidate nurture campaigns for hard-to-fill roles', 'Tracking DEI metrics and EEOC compliance data'],
 NOW()),

('ashby', 'Ashby', 'All-in-one hiring platform with the best analytics in the category',
 'Ashby is a modern all-in-one recruiting platform that combines ATS, CRM, scheduling, and analytics in a single product. Where it stands out is analytics: Ashby tracks recruiting metrics at a depth that legacy platforms cannot match, including interviewer-level throughput, source-of-hire attribution down to campaign level, and offer acceptance rates segmented by role, team, and salary band. The scheduling module handles complex interview loops automatically - sending availability requests, coordinating panel schedules, and sending confirmation emails without recruiter coordination. The AI writing assistant generates job descriptions, candidate outreach emails, and interview plans from a brief. Ashby is a favorite at high-growth startups that need enterprise-grade data without the enterprise price tag or implementation complexity of Greenhouse or Workday Recruiting. Companies like Notion, Linear, Vercel, and Brex use Ashby. For recruiting operations teams that run on data and want to improve hiring quality through measurement rather than intuition, Ashby is the most powerful option currently available.',
 'https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=ashbyhq.com&sz=64',
 'https://ashbyhq.com', 'https://ashbyhq.com',
 ARRAY['recruiting', 'hr-tech'],
 'paid', false, 0.00,
 4.7, 847, true, true, false,
 ARRAY['Best recruiting analytics in the market by a significant margin', 'Automated interview scheduling that handles complex panel loops', 'All-in-one: ATS, CRM, scheduling, analytics in one product', 'Favored by high-growth tech companies for data-driven hiring'],
 ARRAY['Newer platform - fewer integrations than Greenhouse', 'Pricing is competitive but not cheap for small teams', 'Some advanced features require onboarding support'],
 ARRAY['Building data-driven recruiting operations at high-growth startups', 'Automating complex multi-stage interview scheduling loops', 'Tracking source ROI and interviewer performance at depth'],
 NOW()),

('rippling', 'Rippling', 'HR, IT, and Finance unified in one workforce platform',
 'Rippling is a workforce management platform that unifies HR, IT, and Finance in a single system. When a new hire is added in Rippling, the platform automatically provisions their laptop software, email account, Slack access, and payroll - without any manual coordination between HR and IT. This automated provisioning and deprovisioning is the defining differentiator: when an employee leaves, Rippling deactivates all their access simultaneously with their last day. The PEO option allows small companies to offer Fortune 500 benefits by pooling with Rippling employees. Global payroll runs in 50+ countries from the same interface as US payroll. The ATS module handles recruiting, and an LMS handles onboarding and compliance training. For startups scaling from 10 to 500 employees where HR processes are being built for the first time, Rippling reduces the administrative overhead of managing multiple disconnected HR, payroll, and IT systems. Rippling is priced per employee per month and scales with headcount.',
 'https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=rippling.com&sz=64',
 'https://rippling.com', 'https://rippling.com',
 ARRAY['hr-tech', 'productivity'],
 'paid', false, 8.00,
 4.6, 3124, false, true, false,
 ARRAY['Automatic software provisioning when new hires are onboarded', 'Unified HR, IT, and Finance in one platform', 'Global payroll in 50+ countries', 'PEO option for competitive benefits at small company scale'],
 ARRAY['Can be complex to configure for non-standard workflows', 'Customer support response times vary', 'Full value requires using HR, IT, and Finance modules together'],
 ARRAY['Automating IT provisioning and deprovisioning for growing teams', 'Running global payroll and benefits from a single system', 'Building HR infrastructure at startups scaling from 10 to 500 people'],
 NOW()),

('bamboohr', 'BambooHR', 'HR software built specifically for small and medium businesses',
 'BambooHR is an HR information system designed for the 10-to-500 employee range, covering employee records, onboarding, time tracking, performance management, and basic payroll. Where enterprise platforms like Workday or SAP SuccessFactors are overkill for SMBs, BambooHR provides the core HR capabilities a growing company needs without the implementation complexity or per-module pricing. The self-service portal lets employees update their own information, request time off, and complete onboarding checklists - reducing routine HR administrative tasks. Performance management features include goal setting, 360-degree feedback, and automated review scheduling. The ATS handles basic recruiting workflows for companies hiring at a moderate pace. Reporting covers headcount, turnover, time-to-hire, and compensation analysis with export to Excel or direct visualization. BambooHR is not the most feature-rich HR platform, but it is consistently rated the highest for ease of use and customer support in the SMB segment, making it the default choice for first-time HR software buyers.',
 'https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=bamboohr.com&sz=64',
 'https://bamboohr.com', 'https://bamboohr.com',
 ARRAY['hr-tech', 'productivity'],
 'paid', false, 0.00,
 4.5, 2673, false, false, false,
 ARRAY['Purpose-built for SMB - not a stripped-down enterprise tool', 'Consistently top-rated for ease of use and customer support', 'Employee self-service reduces routine HR admin work', 'Strong onboarding checklists and e-signature for new hire paperwork'],
 ARRAY['Payroll is a paid add-on, not included in base price', 'Limited customization compared to enterprise HRIS platforms', 'ATS is basic - not suitable for high-volume or complex hiring'],
 ARRAY['Centralizing employee records for companies with 10-500 employees', 'Automating onboarding paperwork and checklists for new hires', 'Running performance reviews and goal tracking without spreadsheets'],
