('goodtime', 'GoodTime', 'AI-powered interview scheduling that eliminates recruiter coordination overhead',
 'GoodTime automates the most time-consuming part of recruiting: interview scheduling. For a candidate moving through a 4-stage loop with a panel of 6 interviewers, scheduling can consume hours of recruiter time per candidate across email chains, calendar conflicts, and rescheduling requests. GoodTime replaces this entirely by reading interviewer availability, applying scheduling preferences (no back-to-back, no early morning), and sending candidates a self-scheduling link that respects all constraints automatically. When a candidate reschedules, GoodTime recalculates the entire loop. Interviewer pools ensure that no single interviewer is overburdened and that diversity of perspective is maintained across panels. Hiring velocity analytics show which interview stages cause the most drop-off and delay, giving recruiting teams data to optimize their processes. Companies using GoodTime report significant reductions in time-to-schedule and scheduler workload. For recruiting operations at companies hiring 50+ people per quarter, the time savings justify the cost immediately.',
 'https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=goodtime.io&sz=64',
 'https://goodtime.io', 'https://goodtime.io',
 ARRAY['recruiting', 'scheduling'],
 'paid', false, 0.00,
 4.6, 412, false, true, false,
 ARRAY['Eliminates manual interview scheduling across complex panel loops', 'Interviewer pool management prevents overburdening top interviewers', 'Candidate self-scheduling with real-time calendar sync', 'Hiring velocity analytics pinpoint scheduling bottlenecks'],
 ARRAY['Enterprise pricing - not cost-effective for low-volume hiring', 'Setup requires integration with your ATS and calendar systems', 'Most value at 50+ hires per quarter scale'],
 ARRAY['Automating panel interview scheduling for high-volume tech recruiting', 'Reducing coordinator workload when scheduling complex multi-stage loops', 'Tracking interviewer load balance and scheduling SLA metrics'],
 NOW()),

('beamery', 'Beamery', 'Talent lifecycle platform for strategic workforce planning',
 'Beamery is a talent lifecycle platform that covers three interconnected problems: talent acquisition, talent management, and workforce planning. The AI layer - called TalentGPT - powers skills inference, career pathing recommendations, and talent intelligence that connects internal mobility with external recruiting. When a role opens, Beamery can identify internal candidates likely to succeed before going external. When a candidate applies, it surfaces historical engagement data from previous interactions. The skills taxonomy engine maps every employee and candidate to a standardized skills ontology, enabling workforce planning based on skill gaps rather than headcount spreadsheets. Beamery is built for large enterprises - companies with thousands of employees and complex internal mobility needs where the cost of external hiring versus internal development is a strategic CFO-level question. Clients include Spotify, American Airlines, and EY. For mid-market companies or straightforward ATS needs, Beamery is overkill. For enterprises treating talent as strategic infrastructure, it is one of the most sophisticated platforms available.',
