('metaview', 'Metaview', 'AI interview notes that let interviewers focus on the candidate',
 'Metaview records and transcribes interviews, then uses AI to generate structured interview notes automatically - aligned to the scorecard criteria defined in your ATS. Rather than interviewers taking notes during a conversation (which splits attention and degrades interview quality), Metaview captures everything and presents a summary: candidate answers to each scorecard question, key quotes, and a structured evaluation the interviewer can approve or edit. The AI does not score candidates - it organizes evidence so the interviewer can score with full context rather than reconstructed memory. Integrations with Greenhouse, Lever, and Ashby push notes directly to the candidate record, reducing post-interview admin from 20 minutes to under 2 minutes. For recruiting teams that care about interview quality, Metaview addresses a real problem: interviewers who take notes miss non-verbal signals; those who do not forget details by debrief. The result is more consistent hiring decisions based on actual evidence rather than recency bias.',
 'https://www.google.com/s2/favicons?domain=metaview.ai&sz=64',
